The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 Bengal open campaign vs Nagaland 

Kochi: Bengal will open their campaign in the 60th edition of Santosh Trophy against Nagaland on November 5. The tournaments most successful team has been clubbed in Cluster VIII with Mizoram and Andhra Pradesh, apart from Nagaland. 

On November 7, Bengal ? coached by Aloke Mukherjee and Biswajit Das ? will take on Andhra Pradesh and next face Mizoram after two days. 

The quarter final league matches will be played in Kochi at the Jawaharlal Nehru International Stadium, from November 11. Last years semi-finalists ? Kerala, Services, Punjab, Manipur ? have been seeded direct into the quarter-final stage. 

The teams have been divided into eight clusters and the winners of the clusters will join the four seeded teams into the quarter finals. 

The semi-finals will be played on Nov 17 and 18 while the final is slated for November 20. 

The preliminary matches will be played in Kozhikode and Thiruvananthapuram simultaneously from November 4. 

Fixtures of the matches were released in here on Saturday. 

 (PTI) 




